00:51.160 --> 00:55.518
It is with great sorrow and regret that I can confirm the identity of the officer

00:55.680 --> 00:59.674
killed in the line of duty on Monday in north Belfast.

01:00.640 --> 01:05.236
<i>Detective Sergeant James Olson was a dedicated and hardworking policeman,</i>

01:05.400 --> 01:07.596
<i>liked and respected by his colleagues.</i>

01:08.560 --> 01:13.237
<i>Just 31 years old, he leaves behind a wife and two small children.</i>

01:14.000 --> 01:17.471
<i>On behalf of all the law-abiding citizens of Northern Ireland,</i>

01:17.640 --> 01:23.432
<i>I wish to offer my deep condolences to his family, his friends and his colleagues.</i>

02:03.600 --> 02:05.319
- Danni? <i>- Yes, ma'am?</i>

02:05.480 --> 02:09.872
I got the lab report back on the varnish that was used on Sarah Kay's finger and toenails.

02:10.039 --> 02:13.670
<i>It's called Jezebel Red, it's by Connell, part of their Painted Lady range.</i>

02:13.840 --> 02:15.832
Sold everywhere, unfortunately.

02:17.360 --> 02:19.352
<i>- Right.</i>
- Can you get me some?

02:21.200 --> 02:22.714
The shops aren't open yet.

02:23.680 --> 02:25.672
You'll think of something.

02:38.200 --> 02:40.078
- Daddy!
- Hey.

02:42.680 --> 02:44.637
Eugh, you're sweaty.

02:44.800 --> 02:46.632
I thought you were at work.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.678
I got back early, went for a run.

02:48.840 --> 02:51.355
Instead of being here to help me with the kids?

02:53.360 --> 02:55.750
Must be nice to have all that energy to burn.

02:56.560 --> 02:58.552
Get your things. Time to go.

03:00.240 --> 03:02.232
- Liam!
- Here.

03:09.640 --> 03:13.919
Right, I'm leaving now. If anyone's coming with me, they'd better hurry up.

03:18.400 --> 03:20.392
Bye, Pops.

04:29.480 --> 04:33.713
I took a call on Olson's phone the morning after the shooting from an unregistered mobile.

04:33.880 --> 04:35.553
The number subsequently went dead.

04:35.720 --> 04:38.280
The call came from somewhere inside this hotel.

04:38.440 --> 04:39.954
We checked the register.

04:40.120 --> 04:43.113
A suite was booked in the name of Belfast Events Ltd.

04:43.280 --> 04:46.557
Company director: Aaron Monroe.

04:49.400 --> 04:51.392
This is the next morning.

04:51.840 --> 04:53.832
Breedlove with one of the girls.

04:54.800 --> 04:57.759
The suite has been cleaned at least twice since then.

04:57.920 --> 05:00.958
But we still found traces of Class A drugs and blood.

05:01.120 --> 05:06.434
These two were picked up an hour or so later by Morgan Monroe's driver.

05:07.920 --> 05:13.314
Both Rossmeisl and Lang made substantial contributions to the Alice Monroe fund.

05:22.800 --> 05:25.076
How do Breedlove and Olson fit into this?

05:26.160 --> 05:30.234
Back in the day, Breedlove was Morgan Monroe's close protection officer.

05:30.400 --> 05:33.871
He might have been there moonlighting, providing security.

05:35.200 --> 05:39.194
He might have been there to supply them with the drugs and/or the girls.

05:39.880 --> 05:41.633
Olson, I'm not sure.

05:42.960 --> 05:48.592
It's starting to look like my praise for a dear departed colleague was fabulously premature.

05:49.720 --> 05:51.871
We have a facility on Breedlove's phone.

05:52.040 --> 05:54.509
He put in a call to Aaron Monroe this morning.

05:55.080 --> 05:59.074
He seems to have some concerns that he might meet the same fate as Olson.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.431
Looking at this girl's face,

06:03.160 --> 06:06.232
if she's badly injured, that's a loss of earnings right there.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.710
These girls make ten grand a week, easily.

06:09.520 --> 06:12.957
Breedlove seemed to be suggesting that this has happened before.

06:13.120 --> 06:16.955
He talked about making a payment of 30 grand to someone called Mirko.

06:17.120 --> 06:20.830
The girls flew into Dublin from Heathrow, then came north by road.

06:21.840 --> 06:23.832
I'm making enquiries with the Met.

06:27.680 --> 06:29.478
- Bring him in.
- Breedlove?

06:30.160 --> 06:31.594
Bring him in.

06:40.040 --> 06:41.520
Paul?

06:42.400 --> 06:43.629
Paul!

06:45.680 --> 06:46.955
Paul!

06:53.400 --> 06:55.676
- Did you not hear me calling you?
- When, George?

06:55.840 --> 06:57.718
You just passed me in the corridor.

06:57.880 --> 06:59.872
Did I? Didn't see you.

07:06.120 --> 07:07.713
I have an appointment.

07:07.880 --> 07:10.634
And I've just had James Tyler in here this morning.

07:10.800 --> 07:14.191
To say he was angry would be a considerable understatement.

07:15.040 --> 07:19.353
He says you made an unscheduled house call on his wife when she was home alone.

07:20.960 --> 07:23.270
It wasn't unscheduled. She called, very upset.

07:23.440 --> 07:25.716
Why didn't you have an appointment here?

07:26.400 --> 07:28.790
You know he beats her? She was black and blue.

07:28.960 --> 07:30.952
Then you report it to the police.

07:31.360 --> 07:35.320
There are protocols that you seem to think you can ignore with impunity.

07:35.480 --> 07:38.473
Anyway, she has an appointment. She's coming in today.

07:38.640 --> 07:40.472
It's not in the diary.

07:40.920 --> 07:42.991
I need to make a phone call to confirm.

07:45.000 --> 07:47.834
Did you talk to any of the local residents when you were there,

07:48.000 --> 07:50.310
discuss Mr Tyler's personal business with them?

07:51.640 --> 07:53.518
Does that seem likely?

07:53.680 --> 07:55.000
I don't know.

07:55.160 --> 07:56.560
You tell me.

07:57.480 --> 07:59.153
I asked for some directions.

07:59.320 --> 08:01.915
- Maybe they saw my name tag.
- You bet your life they did.

08:02.080 --> 08:06.279
This is Shankill, not some place you can come and go willy-nilly without being noticed.

08:07.200 --> 08:09.795
- Willy-nilly?
- You know what I mean.

08:17.400 --> 08:19.915
I'd like to talk to Mrs Tyler when she comes in.

08:35.159 --> 08:37.038
<i>Detective Inspector Breedlove?</i>

08:37.200 --> 08:39.192
- Speaking. <i>- It's DCI Eastwood.</i>

08:39.960 --> 08:41.952
<i>I'd like to have a talk with you, Rob.</i>

08:42.840 --> 08:44.832
- When? <i>- Right away, if possible.</i>

08:48.520 --> 08:49.670
What about?

08:49.840 --> 08:54.278
<i>I think you might be able to help me clarify some issues surrounding the murder of James Olson.</i>

08:54.440 --> 08:56.432
<i>I'd appreciate your help.</i>

09:00.480 --> 09:01.994
I'll come in.

09:13.680 --> 09:15.319
I have to go.

09:18.200 --> 09:20.112
Don't be long.

10:17.080 --> 10:22.200
The Mosuo women are a small ethic group living in China on the border with Tibet.

10:23.400 --> 10:25.278
They're a matriarchal society.

10:25.440 --> 10:27.432
Well, matrilineal.

10:27.800 --> 10:31.589
They don't practise traditional marriage, no husbands and wives.

10:32.200 --> 10:34.715
They practise what's called walking marriage.

10:36.320 --> 10:38.789
The partners live in different households.

10:39.440 --> 10:41.079
I'm simplifying.

10:43.040 --> 10:46.920
One of Sarah Kay's work colleagues said she talked about them at the bar

10:47.080 --> 10:49.231
on the night that she called you to the house.

10:50.160 --> 10:54.359
Drinking wine with her friends suggests to me she didn't know she was pregnant.

10:55.600 --> 10:57.478
She didn't tell any of her family

10:57.640 --> 11:01.190
and no one's come forward to say that they're the father.

11:01.360 --> 11:03.875
So I thought maybe it was just a sweet night.

11:04.760 --> 11:06.194
What's that?

11:07.360 --> 11:09.716
It's what the Mosuo women call a secret visit

11:09.880 --> 11:13.794
when a woman asks a man to spend the night and then leave in the morning.

11:15.520 --> 11:17.079
How do you know so much about it?

11:17.240 --> 11:19.232
It's not a secret.

11:23.360 --> 11:25.317
My first degree was in anthropology.

11:25.480 --> 11:28.678
- Your first degree?
- Mm, I have hundreds.

11:31.640 --> 11:33.518
I need you to come in.

11:33.680 --> 11:35.512
<i>I can't.</i>

11:35.680 --> 11:38.559
Liz, I shouldn't have called on you at home like that.

11:38.720 --> 11:40.712
It's against the rules.

11:42.240 --> 11:44.232
My job is on the line.

11:45.240 --> 11:47.232
Jimmy needn't know.

11:48.320 --> 11:50.710
I just want you to come in this afternoon.

11:52.040 --> 11:53.599
<i>I can't.</i>

11:54.480 --> 11:55.709
Why?

11:57.320 --> 11:59.516
<i>I don't want to see anyone at the moment.</i>

12:02.360 --> 12:05.239
Put on a headscarf and some dark glasses.

12:06.120 --> 12:07.998
You'll look like Sophia Loren.

12:08.160 --> 12:09.640
<i>Who's she?</i>

12:13.040 --> 12:15.032
You asked me to hold you, Liz.

12:15.920 --> 12:17.912
And I held you.

12:19.600 --> 12:21.592
Now I'm asking you to do this for me.

13:13.840 --> 13:15.035
Robbie.

13:15.200 --> 13:17.192
Come on through.

13:23.200 --> 13:25.192
Do you want kids?

13:26.160 --> 13:28.117
Maybe one day.

13:29.800 --> 13:31.280
Do you have a man?

13:31.440 --> 13:32.999
A man?

13:34.240 --> 13:35.310
No.

13:42.400 --> 13:43.754
I'm gay.

13:47.360 --> 13:51.639
The neighbours report hearing a hairdryer in the early hours of the morning.

13:51.800 --> 13:53.792
Perhaps he was drying her body.

13:58.360 --> 14:00.352
Perhaps he was drying the nails.

14:15.680 --> 14:18.434
- Where were you when I called you?
- At the Olson's.

14:18.600 --> 14:20.592
How are they? Are they bearing up?

14:21.040 --> 14:23.032
I don't think it's really sunk in yet.

14:23.720 --> 14:27.794
Your phone records show a lot of calls to the Olson home number.

14:30.160 --> 14:32.038
You've pulled my phone records?

14:32.200 --> 14:33.714
Why so many calls?

14:35.280 --> 14:37.954
He was my partner...my friend.

14:40.600 --> 14:44.196
A high proportion of those calls were at times Olson was at work.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.798
Often at work with you.

14:49.520 --> 14:51.512
Were those calls made to Vicky?

14:54.840 --> 14:56.718
Do you know why I joined the police force?

14:56.880 --> 14:58.200
I don't.

14:58.360 --> 15:00.079
That bomb in '87.

15:01.360 --> 15:02.714
Lost his father.

15:02.880 --> 15:05.520
Would have been six at the time, same age as Rory.

15:05.680 --> 15:07.353
I don't remember the name Olson.

15:07.520 --> 15:09.512
His mother remarried.

15:14.000 --> 15:17.118
It was me called his phone that morning when you answered.

15:17.280 --> 15:19.840
Robbie...be careful what you say now.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.913
I had no idea he was already dead, you have to believe me.

15:23.080 --> 15:26.391
You should take legal advice before you say anything more.

15:27.160 --> 15:29.516
Gunned down in the street in front of his son.

15:29.680 --> 15:31.558
Fucking shitbags.

15:31.720 --> 15:33.040
Who?

15:33.200 --> 15:34.714
Who's a shitbag? Mclnturff?

15:34.880 --> 15:36.314
Yes, Mclnturff.

15:38.120 --> 15:39.998
Do you really believe that?

15:40.160 --> 15:42.834
Or was your outburst at the station all for show?

15:47.000 --> 15:49.276
- Have you had someone following me?
- No.

15:49.440 --> 15:51.591
- A car was on my tail here.
- Nothing to do with me.

15:51.760 --> 15:54.400
- You swear?
- I swear.

16:00.600 --> 16:02.478
I'm gonna have to caution you, Rob.

16:02.640 --> 16:05.519
- Are you arresting me?
- We want to get this sorted.

16:06.040 --> 16:07.520
Are you carrying a firearm?

16:07.680 --> 16:08.716
No.

16:08.880 --> 16:11.440
- Where is it?
- It's in my desk drawer.

16:11.600 --> 16:13.159
I had someone check your desk.

16:18.400 --> 16:20.392
If I'd just lost a partner,

16:21.520 --> 16:23.398
and I feared I might be next,

16:23.560 --> 16:25.552
I'd be carrying.

16:28.160 --> 16:30.516
I need to take the weapon from you, Rob. I'm sorry.

16:39.280 --> 16:40.680
It's all right.

16:41.680 --> 16:43.353
I understand.

16:43.520 --> 16:45.591
You're just doing what you have to do.

16:51.600 --> 16:53.796
All of this can be sorted out really easily.

16:53.960 --> 16:55.952
Really, really easily.

17:08.760 --> 17:10.479
Somebody call an ambulance!

17:13.160 --> 17:14.640
Get this woman out.

17:24.560 --> 17:26.551
Matthew, Matthew...

17:27.920 --> 17:29.912
Come with me.

17:33.040 --> 17:34.633
Get everybody out.

17:34.800 --> 17:36.120
Jerry.

17:39.960 --> 17:41.952
Seal these rooms off.

17:44.520 --> 17:45.749
Call Forensics.

17:46.560 --> 17:48.791
Matthew...can you hear me?

17:48.960 --> 17:50.838
Look at me.

17:51.880 --> 17:53.872
Matthew, what happened in there?

17:54.760 --> 17:57.229
- What happened?
- He was handing me his gun.

17:58.400 --> 18:00.915
Then he put it to his face...fired.

18:01.080 --> 18:02.753
- Deliberately?
- Yes.

18:02.920 --> 18:05.594
- It wasn't just a threat and the gun went off?
- No.

18:05.760 --> 18:07.752
No, he meant to do it.

18:08.640 --> 18:10.632
- Do you have your gun on you?
- No.

18:15.160 --> 18:18.153
I'm gonna get a CSI here to take your clothes, all right?

18:18.320 --> 18:20.312
- Yes.
- Right.

18:22.680 --> 18:26.037
We're gonna do this right. We're gonna sort this out.

18:35.080 --> 18:37.072
Do you feel afraid at home?

18:43.320 --> 18:45.312
It's unacceptable, Liz.

18:46.520 --> 18:49.433
You have the right to feel safe in your own home.

18:50.280 --> 18:51.839
I start it.

18:52.440 --> 18:54.113
I throw things at him.

18:54.280 --> 18:56.272
I provoke him.

18:59.360 --> 19:01.238
Even if that's true,

19:01.400 --> 19:05.838
the responsibility for domestic violence always lies with the abuser, Liz.

19:06.880 --> 19:08.872
Never with the abused.

19:10.760 --> 19:12.752
He wasn't always like this.

19:15.280 --> 19:17.272
It's been since Danny died.

19:26.000 --> 19:27.878
You're wearing a long-sleeved top.

19:28.040 --> 19:30.032
That's unusual for you.

19:32.560 --> 19:34.153
Are you self-harming?

19:34.320 --> 19:35.913
No.

19:37.760 --> 19:39.592
Does he force you sexually?

19:56.080 --> 19:58.834
As your counsellor, Liz, I'm not supposed to give advice.

19:59.000 --> 20:00.992
But these people can.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.513
He's out of prison on licence.

20:13.480 --> 20:16.359
If I call the police, he'll go straight back to jail.

20:18.400 --> 20:20.392
I can't do that to him.

20:22.640 --> 20:24.040
Liz...

20:24.640 --> 20:27.838
under the Domestic Violence Crime And Victims Act,

20:28.000 --> 20:31.516
charges can be brought against your husband without your permission.

20:32.520 --> 20:34.512
I can make the call.

20:36.480 --> 20:39.598
But it's important for you that you do it yourself.

20:41.680 --> 20:44.354
They can arrange a shelter until he's arrested.

20:48.240 --> 20:49.959
I'm offering you a lifeline.

20:52.920 --> 20:54.320
Take it.

21:21.600 --> 21:23.000
Can we talk?

21:23.160 --> 21:24.833
I have to wash.

21:25.000 --> 21:26.673
I'll come with you.

21:36.400 --> 21:40.076
It seems Breedlove was having an affair with James Olson's wife.

21:42.480 --> 21:44.472
Why are you telling me?

21:46.120 --> 21:47.998
I thought it might help...

21:48.160 --> 21:50.152
if you were feeling at all guilty.

21:50.680 --> 21:52.114
I'm not.

21:53.680 --> 21:55.717
It's unclear whether Olson knew or not,

21:56.760 --> 21:58.752
whether he suspected anything.

22:03.120 --> 22:05.112
How was he when he was with you?

22:05.960 --> 22:07.838
Fine. We've been over this.

22:08.000 --> 22:10.754
But the text messages, picture images,

22:10.920 --> 22:12.877
breaching the cordon at a crime scene.

22:13.040 --> 22:14.918
They all surprise me.

22:15.080 --> 22:16.878
I read him wrong.

22:17.040 --> 22:18.918
In what way?

22:19.080 --> 22:22.596
I thought he was the type to accept it for what it was and move on.

22:23.840 --> 22:25.479
A sweet night.

22:26.640 --> 22:27.869
What?

22:29.360 --> 22:30.476
Nothing.

22:33.440 --> 22:36.797
Do you have any idea of the effect you have on men?

22:39.360 --> 22:41.352
I'd have left my wife...

22:42.680 --> 22:44.478
..my kids...

22:45.520 --> 22:47.318
..everything for you.

22:49.920 --> 22:51.912
That would have been a mistake.

22:59.080 --> 23:00.196
I'm sorry.

23:02.640 --> 23:04.632
I shouldn't have said that.

23:07.320 --> 23:09.312
I'm sorry.

23:13.320 --> 23:16.518
Thank you...for handling things so calmly.

23:18.280 --> 23:20.272
And so efficiently.

23:59.640 --> 24:01.120
Boss?

24:02.400 --> 24:04.995
All three victims are on professional websites,

24:05.160 --> 24:07.038
all have a detailed profile,

24:07.200 --> 24:09.795
all with a professional portrait photograph.

24:11.080 --> 24:12.958
Maybe this is how he finds them.

24:13.120 --> 24:16.796
If the killer's trawling professional websites looking for victims,

24:16.960 --> 24:19.680
should we do the same to identify potential targets?

24:20.560 --> 24:22.438
I'm not sure we can.

24:22.600 --> 24:26.799
If we do identify women who we think conform to the killer's type, what do we do?

24:26.960 --> 24:28.952
- Warn them.

24:29.800 --> 24:33.476
If we warn them, we have to protect them and we don't have the resources.

24:35.160 --> 24:37.038
- Hello? <i>- Hi, it's me.</i>

24:37.200 --> 24:41.353
<i>The crime scene is being released back to the family and I'd like to take another look.</i>

24:41.520 --> 24:43.398
- When? <i>- Now.</i>

24:43.560 --> 24:45.552
I'll meet you there.

25:06.360 --> 25:08.352
Mrs Shergold and I would like a word.

25:09.720 --> 25:10.836
When?

25:11.000 --> 25:12.320
Now.

25:22.560 --> 25:25.712
Home visiting can be very useful from a diagnostic point of view.

25:25.880 --> 25:27.758
It's in breach of department guidelines.

25:27.920 --> 25:32.199
Seeing someone in their home can provide unexpected information about their psyche.

25:32.360 --> 25:34.477
Paul...please.

25:35.360 --> 25:36.919
"Paul...please"?

25:37.080 --> 25:40.232
Mrs Shergold is in complete agreement with me over this matter.

25:40.400 --> 25:43.871
The protocols are in place to protect you as well as the clients.

25:44.040 --> 25:46.794
We simply cannot tolerate any further indiscipline.

25:46.960 --> 25:49.873
Consider this an official warning. You'll be receiving a letter.

25:50.040 --> 25:53.272
<i>- You'll</i> be receiving a letter.
- What?

25:53.440 --> 25:54.669
What?

25:56.320 --> 25:57.993
I'm sorry, I'm not following.

25:58.160 --> 26:00.152
I'm sorry, <i>I'm</i> not following.

26:02.000 --> 26:05.232
- Are you taking this seriously?
- Are <i>you</i> taking this seriously?

26:05.400 --> 26:07.278
I don't understand.

26:07.440 --> 26:09.432
Then let me explain.

26:10.360 --> 26:12.238
I've just done a good thing.

26:12.400 --> 26:14.278
A very good thing.

26:14.440 --> 26:17.319
And thanks to me, Liz Tyler can sleep safe tonight.

26:18.040 --> 26:20.191
You people should be congratulating me,

26:20.360 --> 26:23.273
not bleating on about petty rules and regulations.

26:30.480 --> 26:33.552
Where was he hiding, do you think...

26:35.000 --> 26:36.992
..when he first attacked her?

26:38.480 --> 26:40.153
In here?

26:53.560 --> 26:55.199
Or from here?

26:56.600 --> 26:58.478
<i>She's at the top of the stairs.</i>

26:58.640 --> 27:01.235
<i>He comes out fast, overpowers her.</i>

27:03.440 --> 27:05.432
<i>So he lifts her...</i>

27:06.760 --> 27:09.753
..carries her, struggling, into the bedroom.

27:10.920 --> 27:13.958
He gets her onto the bed, pins her down.

27:14.120 --> 27:16.112
Then he ties her to the bed frame.

27:17.160 --> 27:20.551
The ligature marks suggest maybe here and there.

27:23.280 --> 27:27.354
